text:
If we look 
for the rst words of wisdom reaching us from our ancestors, 
5,000 years ago, we're in for a big disappointment.

The only humanist sect that has actually broken loose 
from traditional monotheism is evolutionary humanism, 
whose most famous representatives are the Nazis.

Lawyers need to rethink issues of privacy and identity; 
governments are faced with rethinking matters of health 
care and equality; sports associations and educational 
institutions need to rede ne fair play and achievement; 
pension funds and labour markets should readjust to a world 
in which sixty might be the new thirty.
